defs.docs: This crate gives small utilities for casting between plain data types.

defs.name: Zeroable
defs.docs:
Trait for types that can be safely created with
 [`zeroed`](core::mem::zeroed).

defs.name: zeroed
defs.docs: Calls [`zeroed`](core::mem::zeroed).

defs.name: Pod
defs.docs: Marker trait for "plain old data".

defs.name: Contiguous
defs.docs: A trait indicating that:

defs.name: Int
defs.docs:
The primitive integer type with an identical representation to this
 type.

defs.name: MAX_VALUE
defs.docs: The upper *inclusive* bound for valid instances of this type.

defs.name: MIN_VALUE
defs.docs: The lower *inclusive* bound for valid instances of this type.

defs.name: from_integer
defs.docs:
If `value` is within the range for valid instances of this type,
 returns `Some(converted_value)`, otherwise, returns `None`.

defs.name: into_integer
defs.docs:
Perform the conversion from `C` into the underlying integral type. This
 mostly exists otherwise generic code would need unsafe for the `value as
 integer`

defs.name: TransparentWrapper
defs.docs:
A trait which indicates that a type is a `repr(transparent)` wrapper around
 the `Wrapped` value.

defs.name: wrap_ref
defs.docs: Convert a reference to a wrapped type into a reference to the wrapper.

defs.name: wrap_mut
defs.docs:
Convert a mut reference to a wrapped type into a mut reference to the
 wrapper.

defs.name: bytes_of
defs.docs: Re-interprets `&T` as `&[u8]`.

defs.name: bytes_of_mut
defs.docs: Re-interprets `&mut T` as `&mut [u8]`.

defs.name: from_bytes
defs.docs: Re-interprets `&[u8]` as `&T`.

defs.name: from_bytes_mut
defs.docs: Re-interprets `&mut [u8]` as `&mut T`.

defs.name: try_from_bytes
defs.docs: Re-interprets `&[u8]` as `&T`.

defs.name: try_from_bytes_mut
defs.docs: Re-interprets `&mut [u8]` as `&mut T`.

defs.name: TargetAlignmentGreaterAndInputNotAligned
defs.docs:
You tried to cast a slice to an element type with a higher alignment
 requirement but the slice wasn't aligned.

defs.name: OutputSliceWouldHaveSlop
defs.docs:
If the element size changes then the output slice changes length
 accordingly. If the output slice wouldn't be a whole number of elements
 then the conversion fails.

defs.name: SizeMismatch
defs.docs:
When casting a slice you can't convert between ZST elements and non-ZST
 elements. When casting an individual `T`, `&T`, or `&mut T` value the
 source size and destination size must be an exact match.

defs.name: AlignmentMismatch
defs.docs:
For this type of cast the alignments must be exactly the same and they
 were not so now you're sad.

defs.name: PodCastError
defs.docs: The things that can go wrong when casting between [`Pod`] data forms.

defs.docs: As `align_to_mut`, but safe because of the [`Pod`] bound.

defs.docs: Try to convert a `&T` into `&U`.

defs.name: try_cast_mut
defs.value: fn <A, B> (a: &mut A) -> Result<&mut B, PodCastError>
defs.docs: Try to convert a `&mut T` into `&mut U`.

defs.docs: Try to convert `&[T]` into `&[U]` (possibly with a change in length).
